neutral.name: Neutral Space
neutral.desc: This space can be freely traversed and have no additional effects.

shop.name: Shop
shop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random item, if there is room in the player's inventory.

altar.name: Altar
altar.desc: A player on this space is allowed to make one wish. At the end of the turn, all players who made wishes have their wishes granted and then are returned to Start. Multiple players on this space do not engage in combat.

start.name: Start Square
start.desc: All new players start on this square. Players sharing this space do not fight, and any player on this space does not lose HP for any reason. A player who ends his turn on Start is cured of any status ailments.

gap.name: Empty Gap
gap.desc: These spaces are ordinarily impassible to players. If a player is forced onto a gap, they immediately return to Start and loses 5 HP. A player who is adjacent to a gap can choose to leap into the gap.

crumbled.name: Crumbled Space
crumbled.desc: When a player steps off this space, it crumbles and disappears. Any item on this space is removed from the game board when it does so.

bank.name: Bank Tile
bank.desc: A player who passes this space can interact with the bank. Each player has their own personal vault in the bank. A player can deposit items into their personal vault. At the same time, the player can withdraw items from the vault. A player can withdraw at most as many items as they deposited on the current turn. Even if this space disappears or moves, the items are kept safe in a vault. All Bank Tiles share the same collection of vaults.

bowser.name: Bowser Space
bowser.visual: dark red space with Bowser space icon
bowser.desc: A player who lands on this space will suffer a penalty as decided by Mercerenies.

toaster.name: Toaster Space
toaster.visual: light blue space with toaster image
toaster.desc: Every few turns, at the end of the turn, this space will shoot toast at the nearest player. That player will be shot backward a few spaces. The toast will never launch a player off the game board. Additionally, targeted players will be allowed to keep the toast, provided there is room in their inventory.

water.name: Water Space
water.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here.

whirl.name: Whirlpool Space
whirl.visual: blue space with watery texture and light blue swirl
whirl.desc: A player who stops here moves in counterclockwise order to the next Whirlpool Space. This space is also treated as a Water Space.

port.name: Port Tile
port.visual: blue space with watery texture and gray/white boat
port.desc: This tile counts as a Water Space. This tile must always border at least one water space and one traversable non-water space. If this condition is not satisfied, this space becomes an ordinary Water Space. This space spawns a Ferryman upon its creation and, if its Ferryman is ever destroyed, spawns another one to replace him.

tneut.name: Tainted Neutral Space
tneut.visual: empty gray space with tainted border
tneut.desc: This space requires 2 movement points to move onto. This space is Tainted.

lava.name: Lava Space
lava.visual: red space with yellow lava texture
lava.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. A player who stops on this space takes 2 damage (mitigated by DEF). This space will never reduce HP to less than 1.

lbowser.name: Lava Bowser Space
lbowser.visual: dark red space with Bowser space icon and lava texture
lbowser.desc: A player who lands on this space will suffer a penalty as decided by Mercerenies. Also, because this space is made of lava, whenever someone lands on it, it will spread and turn nearby spaces into Lava Bowser Spaces.

lshop.name: Lava Shop
lshop.visual: blue space with white 'S' covered in lava texture
lshop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random lava-themed item, if there is space in their inventory.

lneut.name: Lava Neutral Space
lneut.visual: gray space covered with lava texture
lneut.desc: A player who passes this space takes 2 damage (mitigated by DEF). This space will never reduce HP to less than 1.

tlneut.name: Tainted Lava Neutral Space
tlneut.visual: dark gray space with tainted border and lava texture
tlneut.desc: This space requires 2 movement points to move onto. A player who passes this space takes 2 damage (mitigated by DEF). This space will never reduce HP to less than 1.

ltoast.name: Lava Toaster Space
ltoast.visual: light blue space with toaster image and lava texture
ltoast.desc: Some people eat toast with cinammon on it. Some people eat toast with jam on it. Only the most hardcore eat toast with lava on it. A player who lands on this space gets Lava Toast. This space will then turn into a Lava Neutral Space.

obsid.name: Obsidian Space
obsid.desc: This space has no effect when landed on. However, obsidian is an exceedingly strong material, so items, spaces, and other effects cannot transform or destroy this space. This restriction does not apply to wishes.

oport.name: Obsidian Port
oport.visual: gray space with obsidian texture and gray/white boat
oport.desc: This space counts as an Obsidian Space. This space spawns a Lava Ferryman upon its creation and, if its Lava Ferryman is ever destroyed, spawns another one to replace him. The Lava Ferryman is spawned on the nearest Lava Space.

lbank.name: Lava Bank Tile
lbank.visual: yellow-green space with gray vault covered in lava texture
lbank.desc: This space behaves like a Bank Tile. However, when a player withdraws their items from this space, the item that comes back will be a lava-themed variant of the original.

tltoast.name: Tainted Lava Toaster Space
tltoast.visual: light blue space with inverted toaster image, lava texture, and tainted border
tltoast.desc: A player who lands on this space gets Lava Toast. This space will then turn into a Tainted Lava Neutral Space. However, there is a 25% chance that the Lava Toast will actually be sentient and, instead of entering the player's inventory, will attack the player.

ambush.name: Ambush Space
ambush.visual: dull pink space with white upward arrow
ambush.desc: When a player or token lands on this space, a Trap token is created at this space whose ATK is equal to the ATK of the player or token. No Trap is created if the token does not have an ATK stat.

grass.name: Grass Tile
grass.desc: All players who end their turn on this space gain 1 HP. Players on a Grass Tile do not fight one another.

poison.name: Poison Tile
poison.desc: A player who lands on this space loses 3 HP and is afflicted with Poison. A player who passes this space is still afflicted with Poison.

ice.name: Ice Tile
ice.visual: light blue space with white streaks
ice.desc: When a player steps onto this space, they will keep moving in the same cardinal direction until they encounter an impassable space or cease to be moving along ice. The sliding does not cost any additional movement points, aside from the movement point(s) spent moving onto the Ice Tile.

tlbowser.name: Tainted Lava Bowser Space
tlbowser.visual: red-ish space with Bowser space icon, lava texture, and tainted border
tlbowser.desc: A player who lands on this space will suffer a penalty as decided by Mercerenies. Also, because this space is made of lava, whenever someone lands on it, it will spread and turn nearby spaces into Tainted Lava Bowser Spaces. Finally, any player who passes this space will become Ultra Tainted.

tlava.name: Tainted Lava Space
tlava.visual: red space with lava texture and tainted border
tlava.desc: A player who lands on this space must stop here. A player who passes this space takes 2 damage (mitigated by DEF). This space will never reduce HP to less than 1. There is a 10% chance that the player landing on this space will drown and be sent back to start after taking the damage.

tobsid.name: Tainted Obsidian Space
tobsid.visual: gray space with obsidian texture and tainted border
tobsid.desc: Obsidian is an exceedingly strong material, so items, spaces, and other effects cannot transform or destroy this space. This restriction does not apply to wishes. A player who lands on this space becomes Obsidian.

hneut.name: Hallowed Neutral Space
hneut.desc: This space is treated as a neutral space. It cannot become Tainted.

hlava.name: Hallowed Lava Space
hlava.visual: red space with yellow lava texture and hallowed border
hlava.desc: This space is treated as a lava space. A player who moves onto this space must stop here. A player who stops on this space takes 2 damage (mitigated by DEF). This space will never reduce HP to less than 1. It cannot become Tainted.

hwater.name: Hallowed Water Space
hwater.visual: blue space with watery texture and hallowed border
hwater.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. This space is treated as a water space and cannot become Tainted.

hbowser.name: Hallowed Bowser Space
hbowser.visual: dark red space with Bowser space icon and hallowed border
hbowser.desc: A player who lands on this space will suffer a penalty as decided by Mercerenies. This space will never become Tainted.

cice.name: Cracked Ice Tile
cice.visual: light blue space with white streaks and dark blue cracks
cice.desc: When a player steps onto this space, they will keep moving in the same cardinal direction until they encounter an impassable space or cease to be moving along ice. The sliding does not cost any additional movement points, aside from the movement point(s) spent moving onto the Cracked Ice Tile. When a player leaves this space, it becomes a Water Space. This space is treated as an Ice Tile.

hobsid.name: Hallowed Obsidian Space
hobsid.visual: gray space with obsidian texture and hallowed border
hobsid.desc: Obsidian is an exceedingly strong material, so items, spaces, and other effects cannot transform or destroy this space. This restriction does not apply to wishes. This space cannot become Tainted.

tlshop.name: Tainted Lava Shop
tlshop.visual: blue space with white 'S' covered in lava texture and tainted border
tlshop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random lava-themed item, if there is space in their inventory. The lava item cannot be dropped and must be used on the next turn or it will start dripping lava and causing harm to the person holding it. This space is Tainted.

tpoison.name: Tainted Poison Tile
tpoison.visual: purple space with poisonous bubbles and tainted texture
tpoison.desc: A player who passes this space is afflicted with Deadly Poison. This space is Tainted.

tambush.name: Tainted Ambush Space
tambush.visual: dull pink space with white upward arrow and tainted texture
tambush.desc: When a player or token lands on this space, a Trap token is created at this space whose ATK is equal to twice the ATK of the player or token. No Trap is created if the token does not have an ATK stat. This space is Tainted.

tcice.name: Tainted Cracked Ice Tile
tcice.visual: light blue space with white streaks, dark blue cracks, and tainted texture
tcice.desc: When a player steps onto this space, they will keep moving in the same cardinal direction until they encounter an impassable space or cease to be moving along ice. The sliding does not cost any additional movement points, aside from the movement point(s) spent moving onto the Tainted Cracked Ice Tile. When a player leaves this space, it becomes a Tainted Water Space. This space is treated as an Ice Tile. There is a 50% chance that, upon entering this space, it will crack immediately and become Tainted Water. This space is Tainted.

viodeath.name: Instant and Violent Death Space
viodeath.visual: white space with black skull and crossbones
viodeath.desc: A player who passes this space must stop on it. A player who stops on this space loses all their items and then takes 999 damage immediately (mitigated by DEF). A player who stops on a space adjacent to this has a 50% chance of getting pulled onto this space.

hport.name: Hallowed Port Tile
hport.visual: blue space with watery texture, gray/white boat, and hallowed texture
hport.desc: This tile counts as a Water Space. This tile must always border at least one water space and one traversable non-water space. If this condition is not satisfied, this space becomes an ordinary Water Space. This space spawns a Ferryman upon its creation and, if its Ferryman is ever destroyed, spawns another one to replace him. This space will never be Tainted.

twater.name: Tainted Water Space
twater.visual: blue space with watery texture and tainted border
twater.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. This space counts as a Water Space and is Tainted. A player who stops on this space has a 10% chance of drowning and returning to the start square.

barracks.name: Barracks
barracks.visual: orange space with white castle structure
barracks.desc: This space cannot be passed, except by airborne units. Each turn, one Barracks will spawn a random army token: Rifleman, Artillery, Medic, Tank, Bomber, Battleship.

tgrass.name: Tainted Grass Tile
tgrass.visual: green space with grassy texture and tainted border
tgrass.desc: All players who end their turn on this space lose 1 HP for every player who ended their turn on a Tainted Grass Tile, including themselves.

bowgift.name: Bowser's Gift
bowgift.desc: +5 max HP and +2 ATK as long as you hold this item.

ghostsuit.name: Ghost Suit
ghostsuit.desc: You may travel across gaps as part of your movement. A movement onto a gap costs 2 movement points. If you end your turn on a gap, you will still fall off the board.

toast.name: Toast
toast.desc: Yum! Delicious toast. Can be eaten to restore 3 HP. Alternatively, it's really hot, so you could throw it in a cardinal direction to inflict damage to the first player it hits.

transform.name: Transformation Orb
transform.desc: Single use. Transforms the player into a character from Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn, replacing all the user's stats with that character's stats. Additionally, the character's signature item may be given to the player.

hasteboots.name: Boots of Haste
hasteboots.desc: +3 MOV as long as you hold this item.

basher.name: Proper Basher
basher.desc: +2 ATK as long as you hold this item. You can also break stone walls.

trauma.name: Trauma Plate
trauma.desc: +3 DEF as long as you hold this item.

gilded.name: Gilded Sword
gilded.desc: +2 ATK as long as you hold this item. When you are involved in a melee, enemy DEF is ignored.

burnt.name: Burnt Toast
burnt.desc: Yum! Delicious toast. Except that it's burnt. You don't want to eat this, and it's also effectively worthless. However, dropping it requires you to take it out of your inventory, which will burn your hands and cost you 3 HP.

lightw.name: Lightweight Boots
lightw.desc: As long as you are wearing these, any space effects that occur when you pass a space are optional. Effects that occur when you land on a space will still occur normally.

powder.name: Purification Powder
powder.desc: Single use. Can be used on the current space or a token occupying the current space. The target is no longer Tainted.

igboard.name: Interactive Game Board
igboard.desc: Single use. You may make one wish, as though you were at the Altar.

mecha.name: Mecha Bowser Suit
mecha.desc: Single use. When a player lands on a Bowser Space (or a variant thereof), you may use this item. Instead of Mercerenies, you get to select that player's punishment this turn. You may not use this to affect your own punishment.

cookie.name: Cookie
cookie.desc: This one cookie contains all the power of the universe. By eating it, you recover 1 HP.

effects.name: Amphibious
effects.desc: You are unaffected by the effects of Water Spaces.

effects.name: COWN
effects.desc: Cows don't have hands. Your inventory size cannot exceed two.

effects.name: Reversed
effects.desc: When you try to move left, you will move right and vice versa. When you try to move up, you will move down and vice versa.

effects.name: Poison
effects.desc: -1 HP at the end of each turn. This effect will cure itself after a randomized period of time.

effects.name: Ultra Tainted
effects.desc: Any space you pass becomes Tainted.

effects.name: Obsidian
effects.desc: Obsidian is resilient but heavy. DEF+1, but MOV is halved (rounded down).

effects.name: Armless
effects.desc: As long as you are Armless, you cannot voluntarily drop or give up items.

effects.name: Deadly Poison
effects.desc: -1 HP at the end of the first turn you have this. On each subsequent turn, you lose one more HP than last turn.

item.name: Item
item.desc: Icon used to represent items on the map.

goldcoin.name: Gold Coin
goldcoin.desc: Can be picked up by a player. Always protected from wishes.

muston.name: Muston
muston.desc: Moves clockwise around the outermost edges of the board. Any player who lands on his space gets a choice of one of the following items: Transformation Orb, Boots of Haste, Proper Basher, Vitality Vial, Trauma Plate.

ferryman.name: Ferryman
ferryman.desc: If the Ferryman ever ends up on a non-water space, he will die. Tokens who end on the same space as Ferryman will not attack one another or the Ferryman. If the Ferryman's original Port Tile disappears, the Ferryman too disappears. Before the Ferryman moves, all players (or non-player tokens) on the current space are considered as passengers. After his movement, all of his passengers are moved to his new location. The Ferryman moves according to specific rules. (1) If the Ferryman has passengers, the passenger who has been a passenger for the longest consecutive period of time can control his movement. (2) If the Ferryman lacks passengers and can reach a space with a player or token on it, he will travel toward that space. If there are multiple such valid spaces, he will always prefer Port Tiles. (3) Otherwise, he will move toward the Port Tile that spawned him.

lferryman.name: Lava Ferryman
lferryman.desc: This token behaves identically to a Ferryman, except that he can only move on lava, not water. Additionally, he belongs to an Obsidian Port, not a Port Tile. Players on the same space as the Lava Ferryman do not take damage from the lava.

trap.name: Trap
trap.desc: If a player or token which has an HP stat passes this token, this token will attack it. If a player or token which lacks an HP stat passes this token and this token has nonzero ATK, this token will destroy it. If either of these things occurs, this token is removed at the end of the turn.

tmuston.name: Tainted Muston
tmuston.desc: Moves clockwise around the outermost edges of the board. Any player who lands on his space gets a choice of one of the following items: Transformation Orb, Boots of Haste, Proper Basher, Vitality Vial, Trauma Plate. However, there is a 10% chance that Muston will decide to attack the player instead of giving them the desired item.

bbowser.name: Baby Bowser
bbowser.desc: Does not move. Randomly fires up to four Bullet Bill tokens per turn.

bbill.name: Bullet Bill
bbill.desc: When created, this token selects a target player. Each turn, this token moves toward that target, avoiding fire, lava, and walls. This token can move over gaps freely. If it hits its target, lava, fire, or a wall, then it will explode, turning the current space and all adjacent spaces into Terrain Tiles and dealing 6 damage to anyone on those spaces (NOT mitigated by DEF).

tlferry.name: Tainted Lava Ferryman
tlferry.desc: This token actively pursues and will attack whichever player most recently made a wish. His ferry also flies and can therefore move over any spaces, including gaps, without penalty. Players whom he is not pursuing but who are on the same space as him will move with him, as though he is a normal Ferryman.

rifleman.name: Rifleman
rifleman.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. Damage from this token is mitigated by DEF. After moving, fires at a random token that has HP and is within movement range.

battleship.name: Battleship
battleship.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. Damage from this token is mitigated by DEF. Any token that it encounters during movement is run over, dealing half Battleship's ATK in damage. At the end of movement, fires perpendicular to the direction of last motion, in both perpendicular directions, dealing ATK to the first token that is hit.

bomber.name: Bomber
bomber.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. Damage from this token is mitigated by DEF. This token is airborne, and if it collides with another airborne token, both are instantly killed. After movement, Bomber drops a bomb that explodes and deals ATK damage to every token in a 3x3 square around the Bomber, except airborne tokens.

tank.name: Tank
tank.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. Damage from this token is mitigated by DEF. Any token that it encounters during movement is run over, dealing half Tank's ATK in damage. At the end of movement, fires in the cardinal direction it was last moving, dealing ATK in damage to the first token that is hit.

medic.name: Medic
medic.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. After moving, fires at a random token that has HP and is within movement range. As long as Medic's ATK is negative, the target will be healed.

artillery.name: Artillery
artillery.desc: Targets a square and moves to it, then chooses a new target ad nauseam. Damage from this token is mitigated by DEF. Shoots a random tile after moving, dealing damage to every token there.

rulings.desc: Any Altar wishes occur at the end of the turn, after all player movement is completed.
Effects which target a stat that a token lacks have no effect on the token. For example, a space that deals damage will not affect a token who has no concept of HP.

The specific nature of combat in the case of tokens which are deficient in some stats is this. All involved players or tokens who have an ATK stat will attack all involved players or tokens who have an HP stat. All such attacks happen simultaneously, and in general a token will never attack itself unless otherwise stated.

In general, an action which attempts to move into a gap is considered to be a mistake or a typo, and the player will not be allowed to move into the gap. If the movement into the gap was intentional, this should be specified in the post. This ruling does not apply if the player in question has any equipment that would enable him or her to pass the gaps without the normal penalty.

The larger the magnitude of a wish, the less likely it is to end up in the wisher's favor. That is, a simple wish is likely to go exactly as intended. A large and complicated wish may be interpreted extremely literally and the results may not be what was desired.
